wa211102164.description:
Provides a daily drop-in center for women; no children allowed.

Offers: 

-  Limited emergency food

-  Breakfast and lunch

-  Cooking facilities 

-  Laundry facilities

-  Shower facilities with wheelchair accessibility, grab bars and a shower chair

-  Hygiene kits 



Additionally provides: 

-  Use of computers, internet, fax, phone and copy machine to help with job and housing searches 

-  An address for receiving mail 

-  A kitchen and cooking supplies; women can cook throughout the day up until 3:30pm 



Offers optional ongoing case management services with information, referral and advocacy for various needs. 

Clients are welcome to stay at the center all day or simply drop in for one kind of assistance. 

Food and snacks are usually available throughout the day, not only at mealtimes.

Interpreter services are available by advance request.
wa211102164.name: Women's Drop-In Center

wa211119151.description:
Provides individual, couples and family counseling as well as group therapy, psychiatric assessments and medication prescription and psychological testing;  limited treatment for children.



Agency provides DBHR-certified service(s).
wa211119151.name: Child and Family Services

wa211134271.description:
Matches volunteers with low-income seniors and low-income adults with disabilities in King County to assist with basic household chores such as:

-  Food preparation

-  Grocery shopping

-  Home repairs

-  Housekeeping

-  Laundry

-  Yardwork



May also assist with transportation to medical appointments, grocery stores, food banks and other essential errands.

 

Services are provided based on volunteer availability. 

Due to the high number of requests and limited number of volunteers, may be unable to offer services to all callers.
wa211134271.name: Volunteer Services

wa21156022.description:
Holds clinics at free meal programs and tent cities, providing basic medical care to homeless individuals and families living in south King County and Seattle.

A doctor or nurse provides exams and treatment. Program does not carry narcotics or provide any prescription pain medication. 

Also offers

-  HIV tests, STD, and Hep C tests, pregnancy tests and birth control. 

-  Harm reduction services including clean needles and naloxone overdose prevention kits 

-  Brief counseling sessions and referrals to ongoing mental health care

-  Some sites additionally have mobile dental care (services focus on treating dental pain NOT preventative cleanings).



Some sites additionally have dental care. 

Can also assist homeless people in locating help with: 

-  A doctor's office that can provide follow-up care

-   Enrollment into health insurance

-  Referrals to shelter, food banks, legal assistance and domestic violence programs
wa21156022.name: Mobile Medical Van for Homeless People
wa21156022.provider: Public Health - Seattle & King County - Public Health Centers
